h3. Environment
* Confluence Cloud, Rest API

h3. Steps to Reproduce
Try to create a page in the new editor using a body like:
{code:java}
curl -X POST \
  'https://instance.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content?expand=body.atlas_doc_format' \
  -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  -H 'Authorization: Basic <my token>' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
  "title": "Test Page",
  "type": "page",
  "space": {
    "key": "EC"
  },
  "status": "draft",
  "body": {
    "atlas_doc_format": {"value":"{\"version\":1,\"type\":\"doc\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Some text in a paragraph\"}]}]}"}
  }
}' {code}
and it returns a 200 and creates a page, but the body is left empty.

h3. Expected Results
The body is what is passed in the API.

h3. Actual Results
The body for the created page is empty.

h3. Workaround
Instead of:
{code:java}
 "body": { "atlas_doc_format": {"value":"{\"version\":1,\"type\":\"doc\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Some text in a paragraph\"}]}]}"} }
{code}
use:
{code:java}
 "body": {
    "editor": {
      "value":"{\"version\":1,\"type\":\"doc\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Some text in a paragraph\"}]}]}",
      "representation":"atlas_doc_format"
    }
  }
{code}
which works.

h3. Issue Summary
When a table is with *full-width* on a page and you go to compare the current version with another one, the table width gets changed in the comparison. 

h3. Environment
* Cloud
* New Editing Experience

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Add a table on a page;
# Set the table with *wide* or *full* width;
# Publish the page;
# Edit the page;
# Add some random word and publish it again;
# Go to the *Page History* on this page;
# Compare the current version with the previous one.

h3. Expected Results
In the comparison view, the table has the width according to the published version.

h3. Actual Results
The table has a centered width, which is not the same than the original setting.
h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Summary

The PDF Stylesheet to reduce image size is not working in Confluence Cloud. It's still working with Confluence Server 6.15.6
h3. Environment

Old and New editor
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new page with large images
 # Add the PDF Stylesheet to reduce images in PDF export
{code:java}
{
 -fs-fit-images-to-width: 100%  !important;
}
{code}

h3. Expected Results
 - Large images should fit the width

h3. Actual Results
 - Large images don't reduce their size
 - Images are not exported on PDF if they have the original size

h3. Notes
 - In another case, the icons on the table will not be visible after export. Eg. (/) or (x).
{code:java}
h1, h2 { page-break-before:always; }
table.fixedTableLayout {
    table-layout: fixed !important;
    width: 98% !important;
}
table img.confluence-embedded-image {
    -fs-fit-images-to-width: 100%  !important;
}
img { -fs-fit-images-to-width: 100%  !important; }  
hr {
page-break-before: always;
height: 0px;
width: 0px;
}
.pagetitle h1 { display: none; }
{code}

h3. Workaround
 - None
